criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  women 18-70 years of age;

          -  metastatic or locally advanced breast cancer;

          -  HER2 overexpression;

          -  >= 1 measurable lesion.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  prior treatment for advanced breast cancer;

          -  prior treatment with Herceptin;

          -  bone or central nervous system metastasis as the only site of disease;

          -  history of another malignancy (except basal cell skin cancer and cancer in situ of
             the uterine cervix, and contralateral breast cancer) within 5 years of study.
